s-multimedia/media/graphicsmm-line.gif \"graphicsmm_line\")  \nA LineGeometry drawn from (10,20) to (100,130)  \n  \n Other simple geometry classes include <xref:System.Windows.Media.LineGeometry> and <xref:System.Windows.Media.EllipseGeometry>. These geometries, as well as more complex ones, can also be created using a <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry> or <xref:System.Windows.Media.StreamGeometry>. For more information, see the [Geometry Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/geometry-overview.md).  \n  \n## See Also  \n [Geometry Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/geometry-overview.md)   \n [Create a Composite Shape](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-create-a-composite-shape.md)   \n [Create a Shape by Using a PathGeometry](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-create-a-shape-by-using-a-pathgeometry.md)","nodes":[{"pos":[12,71],"content":"How to: Create a Line Using a LineGeometry | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"How to: Create a Line Using a LineGeometry | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,59]}]},{"pos":[481,523],"content":"How to: Create a Line Using a LineGeometry","linkify":"How to: Create a Line Using a LineGeometry","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Create a Line Using a LineGeometry","pos":[0,42]}]},{"content":"This example shows how to use the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.LineGeometry&gt;</ph> class to describe a line.","pos":[524,624],"source":"This example shows how to use the <xref:System.Windows.Media.LineGeometry> class to describe a line."},{"content":"A <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.LineGeometry&gt;</ph> is defined by its start and end points.","pos":[625,707],"source":" A <xref:System.Windows.Media.LineGeometry> is defined by its start and end points."},{"pos":[716,723],"content":"Example","linkify":"Example","nodes":[{"content":"Example","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"The following example shows 